headline: AMD (AMD) Earnings Surge 72%, Margin Expansion Reinforces Bullish Growth Narratives
summary: Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) delivered a sharp turnaround in earnings, posting a 72% increase over the past year after averaging a 9.4% annual decline over the past five years. Net profit margins improved to 9.8%, up from 7.5% a year ago, as profitability accelerated. With Wall Street signaling stronger growth ahead and reward signals in the current report, investors are watching how AMD’s expansion story holds up against industry benchmarks and valuation debates. headline: Cornelis CN5000 Networking Supercharges AI/HPC with Lenovo’s EveryScale Platform Integration
summary: WAYNE, Pa., November 06, 2025--Cornelis, a leading provider of intelligent, high-performance networking solutions, today announced the successful qualification and integration of its CN5000 Omni-Path® networking solution across Lenovo’s ThinkSystem V3 and V4 servers. The CN5000 is now a fully supported networking fabric in Lenovo’s EveryScale Solution, empowering customers to deploy tightly integrated, high-performance AI/HPC infrastructure at scale.

headline: OpenAI does not 'want government guarantees' for massive AI data center buildout, CEO Altman says
summary: OpenAI is in the ‌midst of a multi-billion dollar build-out of data center capacity and has entered into deals with chipmakers ranging from Nvidia to AMD as it spends heavily to secure the necessary infrastructure to power AI models.  The startup expects its annualized revenue run rate to grow to ⁠hundreds of billions by 2030,‌ Altman said in a post on social media platform X. The company is looking at commitments of about $1.4 trillion over ‍the next eight years, he added.  David Sacks, the White House artificial intelligence and crypto czar, said earlier on Thursday that there will be no federal bailout for AI, as ⁠U.S. races to cement its position as ​a global leader in the booming technology.
